Account Manager for the US govt (USAID), the US based NGOs, and international donor organizations.

- Responsible for all US client budgets, projects, and contracts;
- Ensure the timely and successful delivery of our solutions according to customer needs, objectives, and SLAs; enabling our customers to monitor donor compliance (USAID, DfiD)
- Enhance department and organization’s reputation by accepting ownership for accomplishing new and different requests; exploring opportunities to add value to job accomplishments;
- Responsible for the team that keeps current clients satisfied and delivers exceptional client service on a day-to-day basis;
- Ensure the submission of qualitative, competitive and compliant bids by the team;
- Develop a trusted advisor relationship with key accounts and customer stakeholders and serve as point of escalation;
- Travel internationally to the US frequently to meet customers and major policy and donor institutions and to Country Offices in LMICs to meet decentralized decision-making units and other parties involved in the upstream and downstream supply chain;
- Communicate clearly the progress of monthly/quarterly initiatives to internal and external stakeholders
- Update job knowledge by participating in educational opportunities in pharma and health sector; reading professional publications; maintaining personal networks; participating in professional organizations;

In 2019, co-workers selected me as the Positive Energizer thanks to my enthousiasm, the successes (and sharing them), and for being an example to colleagues.

The Netherlands-African Business Council (NABC) has always believed in the business and investment opportunities which Africa has to offer. Established in 1946, the NABC has developed to become the central point of entry for Dutch business and investment relations in Africa. 

1. Trade missions to and from many African countries.
2. Networking events, conferences and knowledge sessions on doing business in Africa.
3. Strategic programs to strengthen the positioning and role of Dutch business in Africa.
4. Customized services, such as position papers, advice and individual matchmaking.

As Project Manager I am in charge of various projects within the Business Services team and my activities include amonst others:
- Development and execution of incoming African (presidential) delegations;
- Management of scientific project;
- Professionalisation, standardisation and development of knowledge and networking events;
- Assistance with the activities of member companies in Africa;
- Management and optimalisation of NABC's marketing tools; and
- Recruitment and guidance of new interns.
